                    <span>As a first gerneration recipient of the benefits of Brown v Board of Education, it was enlightning to get a up-close view of the behind the scene goings-on of the attempts to stall and erode the promise of "Brown".  This is a must read for the public..... to be aware of the diabolical machinations that go on in the back rooms of power to attempt to deny the basic and fundamental right to a good education.  <p>Professor Ogletree illustrates that the promise of  "Brown" remains unfulfilled and that we cannot stop fighting the resistance to that promise.</span>
                  
              
